Chavez retains crown 
Mexico's Julio Cesar Chavez retained his World Boxing Council (WBC)
light-welterweight title here Saturday when he stopped Meldick Taylor
of the United States in the eighth round of a scheduled twelve round
contest.
It was the 32-year-old Chavez' 91st victory against one loss and one
draw while Meldrick has now lost four of 36 fights.
